%% Data Flow Diagram: kube-auth-proxy
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Client Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route/Gateway<br/>443/TCP TLS
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant OIDC as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSSO as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Upstream as Upstream App<br/>configurable

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>Route: GET /app
    Route->>AuthProxy: Forward (edge TLS terminated)
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OIDC Provider
    Browser->>OIDC: Authenticate (user credentials)
    OIDC->>Browser: 302 Redirect /oauth2/callback?code=xxx
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=xxx
    AuthProxy->>OIDC: POST /token (Client ID/Secret)
    OIDC-->>AuthProxy: Access Token + ID Token
    AuthProxy->>Browser: Set-Cookie (session)
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward + X-Forwarded-User/Email/Groups
    Upstream-->>Browser: Application Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: OpenShift OAuth Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /app (no session)
    AuthProxy->>OSSO: Discover /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenShift OAuth
    Browser->>OSSO: Authenticate (user credentials)
    OSSO->>Browser: 302 Redirect /oauth2/callback?code=xxx
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=xxx
    AuthProxy->>OSSO: POST /token (Client ID/SA token)
    OSSO-->>AuthProxy: Access Token
    AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~ (Bearer token)
    K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: User info (name, groups)
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward + X-Forwarded-User/Email/Groups
    Upstream-->>Browser: Application Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 3: RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)
    Browser->>RBACProxy: HTTPS Request (Bearer Token / mTLS)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview (SA token)
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Token valid, user identity
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST SubjectAccessReview (SA token)
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: Allowed/Denied
    RBACProxy->>Upstream: Forward + x-remote-user/groups headers
    Upstream-->>RBACProxy: Response
    RBACProxy-->>Browser: HTTPS Response

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 4: Envoy ext_authz (auth mode)
    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway
    Envoy->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/auth (Cookie/Bearer forwarded)
    AuthProxy-->>Envoy: 200 OK (authenticated) or 401 Unauthorized
